This is already implemented. The middleware at `src/middleware.ts:23-31` checks for a session on `/dashboard` and `/settings` and redirects unauthenticated users to `/auth/login`:

```typescript
const protectedPaths = ["/dashboard", "/settings"];
const isProtected = protectedPaths.some((path) => pathname.startsWith(path));

if (isProtected) {
  const session = await auth0.getSession();
  if (!session) {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL("/auth/login", request.url));
  }
}
```

Additionally, the server actions in both `dashboard/actions.ts` and `settings/actions.ts` call `getRequiredUser()`, which double-checks the session and redirects to login if missing — so even direct form submissions are protected.
